Proggraming_1_HW5

Exercise1:  apply a one-way if statement.

Using the Scanner object, write a simple java program to do the following 
1.	asks the user for their age
2.	checks if the age is greater than or equal to 18 
3.	if age >= 18 print “you are an adult”
4.	if age < 18 print “you are a teenager”

*You need to provide the complete source code 



Exercise 2: apply a two-way if statement.

Using the Scanner object, write a simple java program to do the following 
1.	asks the user for their age
2.	checks if the age is greater than or equal to 18 
a.	if age >= 18 print “you are an adult”
b.	if age < 18 print “you are a teenager”

*You need to provide the complete source code 



Exercise 3 : apply a nested if statement.

Using the Scanner object, write a simple java program to do the following 
1.	asks the user for their age
2.	checks if the age is greater than or equal to 18 
a.	if age > 18 print “you are an adult”
b.	if age <= 18 print “you are a teenager”
3.	checks if the age equal 18 print “you need a guardian” 

*You need to provide the complete source code 



Exercise 4 : apply multiple alternative if statements.

Using the Scanner object, write a simple java program to do the following 
1.	asks the user enter their exam score
2.	checks the score, the table below describes the assignment of grades based on an exam score
Exam Score 	Grade Assigned :
4-5 			A
3-3.99		B 
2-2.99		C
1-1.99		D
below 1 	F

3.	print the grade assigned based on the entered score. 

*You need to provide the complete source code 


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution Exercise 1:
import java.util.Scanner;
	public class Lab5 {

		public static void main(String []args) {
			Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
			System.out.print("How old are you");
			int age = input.nextInt();
		
			if (age >=18) {
				System.out.println("yuo are an adult");
			}
			else {
				System.out.println("yuo are a teenager");

	        	}
		}
		
	}




Solution Exercise 2:
import java.util.Scanner;
	public class Lab5 {

		public static void main(String []args) {
			Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
			System.out.print("How old are you");
			int age = input.nextInt();
		
			if (age >=18) {
				System.out.println("yuo are an adult");
			}
			else {
				if (age <18)
				System.out.println("yuo are a teenager");

           		}
		}
		
	}




Solution Exercise 3:

import java.util.Scanner;
	public class Lab5 {

		public static void main(String []args) {
			Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
			System.out.print("How old are you");
			int age = input.nextInt();
		
			if (age >18) {
				System.out.println("yuo are an adult");
			}
			else {
				if (age <=18)
				System.out.println("yuo are a teenager"); 
			}

		if (age ==18);  {
		System.out.println("yuo need a guardian"); 
		}
			
		}
		
	}





Solution Exercise 4:
import java.util.Scanner; 
	public class Lab5 {

		public static void main(String []args) {
			Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
			System.out.println("Enter yuor score");
			int score = input.nextInt();
			
				if (score>=4); {
				System.out.println("A");
			
		} else {
				if (score>=3);
				System.out.println("B");
			
		} else  {
				if (score>=2);
				System.out.println("C");
			
		} else {
				if (score>=1);
				System.out.println("D");
			
		}  {
	else
				System.out.println("F");
		}
		

         	}

	}
